     1	# Smith
     2	
     3	Smith is an etcd-backed, Kubernetes-native autonomous orchestration platform.
     4	
     5	## Purpose
     6	
     7	Smith coordinates autonomous execution loops as a state machine stored in etcd. It is designed to:
     8	
     9	- accept operator ingress requests (direct, GitHub issues, PRD tasks),
    10	- convert each request into a deterministic loop lifecycle (`unresolved -> overwriting -> synced|flatline|cancelled`),
    11	- enforce safe concurrency with per-loop locks and revision-checked state transitions,
    12	- run loop workers as Kubernetes Jobs and preserve execution evidence (journal, handoff, override, audit).
    13	
    14	In this repository, the focus is the MVP control plane, deployment assets, and verification/test harnesses.
    15	
    16	## Philosophy
    17	
    18	Smith intentionally does not personify agents.
    19	
    20	- Agents are modeled as homogeneous and omnicapable execution units, not distinct personalities.
